        "text": "2Kings 6:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but the one (whoever it was) to whom the mishap occurred, as presently related.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The ax head fell.—Heb., and as for the iron, it fell. The subject of the verb is made prominent by being put first in the accusative. It is thus implied that something happened to the iron. Perhaps, however, it is better to consider that the particle, which usually marks the object of the verb, in cases like the present has its etymological meaning of “something” (’eth being regarded as equivalent to yath, and so to yēsh). (See Winer, Chaldäische Grammatik, ed. Fischer.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The ax head fell.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
